<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2026 01:24:23 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>曾经是世界上最大的客轮，这艘跨越大西洋并将移民带到澳大利亚的金属奇迹拥有了新的博物馆</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/once-the-worlds-biggest-passenger-ship-this-metal-marvel-the-ss-great-britain-that-crossed-the-atlantic-and-took-immigrants-to-australia-has-a-new-museum-home-180989130/</link><description>一座专门展示 SS“大不列颠”号故事的新博物馆即将在布里斯托尔开放，该船永久停泊在干船坞中</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 20:34:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/once-the-worlds-biggest-passenger-ship-this-metal-marvel-the-ss-great-britain-that-crossed-the-atlantic-and-took-immigrants-to-australia-has-a-new-museum-home-180989130/</guid></item><item><title>科学家根据奔跑速度对数百种蜘蛛进行了排名。澳大利亚体型巨大、毛茸茸的棕色猎人名列前茅</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-ranked-hundreds-of-spider-species-by-running-speed-australias-huge-hairy-brown-huntsman-came-out-on-top-180989132/</link><description>棕色猎人的冲刺速度最高可达每小时八英里，但它只能保持这个速度不到一秒钟。该研究将有助于更好地了解蜘蛛的进化和生物力学</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 20:02:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-ranked-hundreds-of-spider-species-by-running-speed-australias-huge-hairy-brown-huntsman-came-out-on-top-180989132/</guid></item><item><title>天文学家注意到望远镜图像中出现了一个神秘的斑点。事实证明，它是地球上拍摄到的最暗的系外行星</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/astronomers-noticed-a-mysterious-spot-appearing-in-telescope-images-it-turned-out-to-be-the-faintest-exoplanet-ever-imaged-from-earth-180989133/</link><description>这颗名为 Beta Pictoris d 的气态巨行星十多年来一直隐藏在人们的视线中，直到两个独立团队证实了它的存在</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 19:40:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/astronomers-noticed-a-mysterious-spot-appearing-in-telescope-images-it-turned-out-to-be-the-faintest-exoplanet-ever-imaged-from-earth-180989133/</guid></item><item><title>人工智能音乐已经来了。为了保护人类艺术家，唱片业提出新标签，例如露骨歌词的标签</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/ai-music-is-already-here-to-protect-human-artists-the-record-industry-proposes-labels-for-it-like-those-for-explicit-lyrics-180989128/</link><description>这项提议提出之际，人工智能生成的音乐在流媒体平台上的可用内容中所占的份额越来越大</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 18:47:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/ai-music-is-already-here-to-protect-human-artists-the-record-industry-proposes-labels-for-it-like-those-for-explicit-lyrics-180989128/</guid></item><item><title>古埃及人相信这些新发现的金舌头可以让死者在来世进行交流</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/ancient-egyptians-believed-that-these-newly-discovered-gold-tongues-allowed-the-dead-to-communicate-in-the-afterlife-180989127/</link><description>在亚历山大以西的Marina el-Alamein考古遗址进行的挖掘工作中，出土了大约两打稀有文物，其中包括一件形状像荷鲁斯之眼的文物</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 17:31:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/ancient-egyptians-believed-that-these-newly-discovered-gold-tongues-allowed-the-dead-to-communicate-in-the-afterlife-180989127/</guid></item><item><title>科学家首次实时目睹海底扩张，让他们罕见地一睹神秘的地质过程</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-scientists-witness-the-seafloor-spread-in-real-time-giving-them-a-rare-glimpse-at-a-mysterious-geologic-process-180989123/</link><description>一项新研究显示，2024 年短短几天内，印度洋部分地区的海底下降了约 13 英尺，约 57 亿立方英尺的熔岩上升到地壳表面</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 16:02:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-scientists-witness-the-seafloor-spread-in-real-time-giving-them-a-rare-glimpse-at-a-mysterious-geologic-process-180989123/</guid></item><item><title>天文学家首次在恒星之间的空间中发现了糖，为地球生命起源提供了新线索</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-astronomers-find-sugar-in-the-space-between-stars-providing-new-clues-about-the-origins-of-life-on-earth-180989122/</link><description>糖是 RNA 和 DNA 的重要组成部分，是当今所有已知生物体的基础。在一项新的研究中，在银河系中心附近充满气体和灰尘的云中检测到了糖赤藓酮糖</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-a-first-astronomers-find-sugar-in-the-space-between-stars-providing-new-clues-about-the-origins-of-life-on-earth-180989122/</guid></item><item><title>这块霸王龙化石的拍卖价格可能是有史以来拍卖价格最高的恐龙。科学家担心他们会失去研究它的机会</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-t-rex-fossil-could-fetch-the-largest-sum-of-any-dinosaur-ever-auctioned-scientists-worry-theyll-lose-the-chance-to-study-it-180989114/</link><description>“Gus”的起价为 1900 万美元，这对于公共机构来说是一个很高的价格。研究人员检查私人收藏的标本可能更困难，而且它们实际上不可能包含在顶级科学期刊的研究中</description><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 20:13:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-t-rex-fossil-could-fetch-the-largest-sum-of-any-dinosaur-ever-auctioned-scientists-worry-theyll-lose-the-chance-to-study-it-180989114/</guid></item><item><title>来认识一下 Sak Tahn Waax，一位生活在 1000 多年前的玛雅数学奇才，留下了一个“非常优雅、复杂”的公式</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-sak-tahn-waax-a-maya-math-whiz-who-lived-more-than-1000-years-ago-and-left-behind-a-really-elegant-complex-formula-180989125/</link><description>考古学家首次确认了该文化中一位著名的古典时代数学家和天文学家的身份</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2026 13:03:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-sak-tahn-waax-a-maya-math-whiz-who-lived-more-than-1000-years-ago-and-left-behind-a-really-elegant-complex-formula-180989125/</guid></item><item><title>英国国王的尸骨被移动了几个世纪，最终丢失了。一位研究人员声称他发现了它们的位置——在停车场下面</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-english-kings-bones-were-moved-over-centuries-and-eventually-lost-one-researcher-claims-he-discovered-their-location-under-a-parking-lot-180989121/</link><description>阿尔弗雷德大帝保卫威塞克斯免受维京人的侵害。在修道院的安息地被扰乱后，研究人员多年来一直在寻找他的遗骸</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 20:37:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-english-kings-bones-were-moved-over-centuries-and-eventually-lost-one-researcher-claims-he-discovered-their-location-under-a-parking-lot-180989121/</guid></item><item><title>这些可爱的老鼠是如何在没有其他哺乳动物居住的极高海拔地区生活的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/heres-how-these-adorable-mice-can-live-at-an-extremely-high-elevation-where-no-other-mammal-is-known-to-survive-180989116/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，安第斯叶耳鼠具有适应能力，可以帮助其在海拔 22,000 英尺的寒冷、低氧条件下有效地产生体温</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 18:45:04 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/heres-how-these-adorable-mice-can-live-at-an-extremely-high-elevation-where-no-other-mammal-is-known-to-survive-180989116/</guid></item><item><title>这座拥有 700 年历史的英国教堂差点关闭，但随后牧师在祭坛下发现了藏匿的金币</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-700-year-old-english-church-nearly-closed-but-then-the-vicar-discovered-a-stash-of-gold-coins-under-the-altar-180989120/</link><description>复活节前夕，一盒 20 世纪 90 年代铸造的金条改变了一小群正在努力支付昂贵维修费用的会众的前景</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 18:26:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-700-year-old-english-church-nearly-closed-but-then-the-vicar-discovered-a-stash-of-gold-coins-under-the-altar-180989120/</guid></item><item><title>罗马混凝土是如何延续千年的？拥有 1,900 年历史的厕所提供了有关该材料令人印象深刻的耐用性的新线索</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-has-roman-concrete-lasted-for-millennia-a-1900-year-old-latrine-offers-new-clues-about-the-materials-impressive-durability-180989115/</link><description>一种称为碳化的化学过程有助于密封裂缝，这有助于解释为什么许多古罗马建筑至今仍屹立不倒。研究人员希望这些见解能够带来更好的现代建筑材料</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 15:54:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-has-roman-concrete-lasted-for-millennia-a-1900-year-old-latrine-offers-new-clues-about-the-materials-impressive-durability-180989115/</guid></item><item><title>认识最早的已知“右手”动物，一种生活在大约 5.5 亿年前的类似蠕虫的生物</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-the-first-right-handed-animal-a-worm-like-creature-that-lived-about-550-million-years-ago-180989107/</link><description>化石分析表明，在埃迪卡拉时期，这种生物在现在南澳大利亚的海底蠕动，并且更喜欢右转</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-the-first-right-handed-animal-a-worm-like-creature-that-lived-about-550-million-years-ago-180989107/</guid></item><item><title>古罗马人相信守护神。考古学家刚刚在英格兰北部发现了一个具有 1,600 年历史的罕见雕刻</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/romans-put-their-faith-in-guardian-spirits-archaeologists-just-found-a-rare-1600-year-old-carving-of-one-in-northern-england-180989118/</link><description>被称为“天才”的保护神或神灵被认为能为特定的人、家庭或地方带来好运和繁荣。考古学家在罗马时期的英国并没有发现很多关于他们的描述</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 11:45:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/romans-put-their-faith-in-guardian-spirits-archaeologists-just-found-a-rare-1600-year-old-carving-of-one-in-northern-england-180989118/</guid></item><item><title>托马斯·杰斐逊的《独立宣言》原始草稿现在可以在国会图书馆看到</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/thomas-jeffersons-original-rough-draft-of-the-declaration-of-independence-can-be-seen-at-library-of-congress-180989113/</link><description>新展览展示了该文件的编辑方式，还展出了葛底斯堡演说的早期副本</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jul 2026 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/thomas-jeffersons-original-rough-draft-of-the-declaration-of-independence-can-be-seen-at-library-of-congress-180989113/</guid></item><item><title>世界上最大的运营蒸汽机车重达 120 万磅。现在，历史悠久的火车可能会驶向您的城镇</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-largest-operating-steam-locomotive-in-the-world-weighs-1-